Docs.summary: Represents possible well-known response codes that can be used when sending responses.
Refer accepted. (202)
The Request-URI is incomplete. (484)
The call was not successful, but alternative services are possible. (380)
The Request-URI was ambiguous. (485)
The call leg (that is, call context) does not exist or has been cleaned up. (481)
The server did not understand the event package specified in a "Event" header field. (489)
Bad extension. The Proxy-Require or Require header filed is not understood. (420)
Bad Gateway. (502)
The request could not be understood due to malformed syntax. (400)

The callee's end system was contacted successfully but the callee is busy and does not wish to take the call at this time. This response is returned only if the client knows that no other endpoint will answer the request. Using is the best way to decline an Invite most of the time. (600)
The receiving system was contacted successfully but it is currently not willing or able to take additional calls. (486)
The request could not be completed due to a conflict with the current state of the resource. (409)
The user wants to decline a signaling session everywhere including call routing. (605)

Used when the client wants to decline a signaling invitation at all forked locations. It is rare that a client would want to do this unless it knows somehow that all clients do not want to connect. Using is the best way to decline an Invite most of the time. (603)
The user does not exist anywhere. (604)
A required extension is missing in the Supported header of the request. (421)
The route set of dialog is invalid and must be updated. (430)
Forbidden. The request should not be repeated. (403)
Represents the provisional Call-Forwarded response. (181)
Internal server error. (500)
The expiration time of the resource request is too short. (423)

MemberSignature.Value: .method public static hidebysig bool IsEndToEndProvisional(int32 responseCode) cil managed
Public Shared Function IsEndToEndProvisional (responseCode As Integer) As Boolean

Docs.summary: Returns true if the provisional response code is a provisional, that is not hop by hop.
Docs.returns: Returns true if the response code is a a provisional and not hop by hop; otherwise false.

remarks.para: Most provisional responses are sent end to end between UAS and UAC. This method can be used to filter out those that are exceptions.

Public Shared Function IsHopByHopProvisional (responseCode As Integer) As Boolean

Docs.summary: Returns true if the provisional response code is used on directly connected SIP entities.
Docs.returns: Returns true if the response code is a single hop provisional; otherwise false.

remarks.para: Most provisional responses are sent end to end between UAS and UAC. In many cases the ones that are sent only on 1 hop need to be handled differently.
